CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 15, 1952, pg. 20, reads: "Military Funeral For WAC - Corp. Ann L. Smith 7056 Fletcher Way, the first Pittsburgh Wac to die on foreign soil was accorded full military honors Thursday for the funeral rites. She died Feb. 3 in Army Hospital in Yokohama, Japan. The deceased Wac was a member of Wesley Center AME Zion Church. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Six pallbearers wearing U. S. military uniforms carrying flag draped casket through line of soldiers and women wearing fur coats, for funeral of WAC Corp. Ann L. Smith, at Gaines Funeral Home, Auburn Street, East Liberty
